                           Links to Selected Sites

   This page lists some selected Web sites that are of interest to the
   users of the FSIS Web site. This  is NOT meant to be a comprehensive
   listing of food safety sites. You will be leaving the FSIS server when
   you follow these links; please bring any technical problems to the
   attention of the webmaster at the destination site.

Item Links Pages on the FSIS Web Site

     * Office of Public Health and Science Links Page
       (Federal government, State government, international organizations,
       and others)
     * Links to State Health and Agriculture Departments

Item Sources of Food Safety Information

     * http://www.FoodSafety.gov, a Gateway to Government Food Safety
       Information, is an objective of the National Food Safety Initiative
       designed to help Web users more easily find government information
       on food safety.
     * Food Safety Links, Compiled by USDA/FDA Foodborne Illness Education
       Information Center:
       http://www.nal.usda.gov/fnic/foodborne/fbindex/index.htm

Item Federal Government Partners in Food Safety

     * U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA): http://www.fda.gov

     * U.S. Food and Drug Administration, Center for Food Safety and
       Applied Nutrition (CFSAN):
       http://www.cfsan.fda.gov
          + http://vm.cfsan.fda.gov/~news/whatsnew.html for the food and
            cosmetic announcements and recent additions to the CFSAN Web
            site
          + http://vm.cfsan.fda.gov/~lrd/press.html for the press
            announcements concerning recalls and other food safety
            information for the press
          + FDA Food Code: http://www.cfsan.fda.gov/~dms/foodcode.html
            (includes the 2001 Food Code)

     * U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC):
       http://www.cdc.gov
          + CDC's Food Safety Initiative Web Site:
            http://www.cdc.gov/foodsafety
          + FoodNet Active Surveillance System for Foodborne Illness:
            http://www.cdc.gov/foodnet
          + MMWR (Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report):
            http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr

     * U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA):  http://www.epa.gov
     * Other Agencies of the U.S. Department of Agriculture: See also USDA
       Home Page, http://www.usda.gov
          + Food Safety Research Information Office (FSRIO):
            http://www.nal.usda.gov/fsrio

Item National Food Safety Programs; National Food Safety Information Network

     * National Food Safety Programs Home Page:
       http://vm.cfsan.fda.gov/~dms/fs-toc.html
     * USDA/FDA Foodborne Illness Education Information Center at the
       National Agricultural Library:
       http://www.nalusda.gov/fnic/foodborne/foodborn.htm
     * Public/Private Partnership for Food Safety Education (Fight
       BAC!^): http://www.fightbac.org
     * Food Safety Grants and Requests for Proposals:
       http://www.foodsafety.gov/~fsg/fsggrant.html

Item HACCP Help

     * USDA/FDA HACCP Training Programs and Resources Database
       http://www.nalusda.gov/fnic/foodborne/haccp/index.shtml
     * International HACCP Alliance: http://haccpalliance.org

Item National Archives and Records Administration

     * NARA Home Page: http://www.access.gpo.gov/nara/index.html
     * Database for the 1995-2001 Federal Register:
       http://www.access.gpo.gov/su_docs/aces/aces140.html
     * Code of Federal Regulations: http://www.access.gpo.gov/nara/cfr

